HiveMind ESP32 Swarm Simulator

Build a fully interactive web application called HiveMind Simulator.

The purpose of the application is to simulate a network of ESP32-based nodes communicating with each other and a central controller. This is a software-only simulation and should not interact with real hardware.

Core Concept

Users should be able to:

Create a central controller node.
Add multiple ESP32 nodes to a virtual environment.
Connect nodes to the controller.
Simulate mesh networking between nodes.
Send commands from the controller.
Observe how commands propagate through the network.
Simulate autonomous movement, scanning, mapping, and task allocation.

The simulation should feel like a simplified drone/robot swarm management platform.

